WEBVTT

00:00:01.150 --> 00:00:02.897
Menstruation.

00:00:02.921 --> 00:00:06.878
A simple word describing
a natural biological process,

00:00:06.902 --> 00:00:09.288
weighed down by centuries of stigma,

00:00:09.312 --> 00:00:13.108
has been transformed into something
most of us can only speak about

00:00:13.132 --> 00:00:14.544
in whispers.

00:00:14.568 --> 00:00:15.727
But why?

00:00:15.751 --> 00:00:17.368
As I speak to you right now,

00:00:17.392 --> 00:00:20.444
more than 800 million women
around the world

00:00:20.468 --> 00:00:21.858
are having a period.

00:00:22.231 --> 00:00:24.228
None of us would exist without it,

00:00:24.252 --> 00:00:28.026
and yet it remains an "embarrassing"
subject to broach.

00:00:28.639 --> 00:00:31.598
From my experience and that
of the women around me,